cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.NE 

This paper is about language understanding tasks and measuring human performance on the GLUE benchmark. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the progress made by neural network approaches, indicating a focus on machine learning, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of low-resource sentence classification, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions limited-data regimes, which could be related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
